<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A0101010001">
<title>
Model Code Description
</title>
<ptxt>
The composition of the model code and the description of each digit are as follows.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
The model code is composed of 9 characters.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
The first character indicates body type.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
The 2nd character indicates model series.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
The 3rd character indicates door (3 door, 4 door, etc.).
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
The 4th and 5th characters indicate the combination of engine and transmission.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
The 6th character indicates the grade etc.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
The 7th character indicates the type of model.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
The 8th and 9th characters indicate the market code For example, “71” means market code “E71”.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
The market code is used in this manual for easier and exact distinction the vehicle specification. 
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</servinfosub>
